    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a mechanically sound example of rotary performance, powered by the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine. The powerplant maintains excellent compression across all rotor faces, ensuring a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. The drivetrain features the factory five-speed manual transmission paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential, providing exceptional power delivery to the rear wheels. Its lightweight chassis retains the signature 50/50 weight distribution and aluminum double-wishbone suspension, offering razor-sharp turn-in and lateral stability. Recent service includes a full cooling system overhaul and updated vacuum lines for the turbo control system. The exterior displays a well-preserved finish with minor signs of road use, while the interior remains a focused, tactile environment for the dedicated driver.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
